parameters:
\N<Prostitute>...What's the matter, boy? You'll catch a cold if you stay
in a place like this.

\N<Prostitute>Could it be... you have nowhere to go? Then why not come to
my place?
\N<Prostitute>You have such a cute face... Don't be shy, okay?
\N<Luda Soldier>Huh? What's this? What are you doing here?

\N<Luda Soldier>You're injured, aren't you? Looks like someone gave you a
good beating. Need some medicine?
\N<Riia>...Leave me alone. It's none of your business, mister.

\N<Luda Soldier>What a bratty kid... Wait a sec? Aren't you the captain's
son? I'm sure your name was Riia or something.
\N<Riia>I'm not... that person's son. I am my dad's son.
\N<Luda Soldier>Well, whatever. So, what are you doing here?

\N<Luda Soldier>If you're waiting for your turn, it's going to be a while. I
believe there were about 10 people ahead of you?

\N<Luda Soldier>Heh, speaking of which, I've got to leave for a mission but
I'll be right back. Looks like it's going to be after me for
you, kid.

\N<Riia>You're annoying... It's not like that. I'm waiting here
because I made a promise.

\N<Riia>We said we'd talk leisurely after everything was finished...
That's what she told me.

\N<Luda Soldier>Huh? I don't get what you're saying, but well, do your best,
kid.
Is there anything as ridiculous and uninteresting as this?

The world just a few steps ahead... behind just one door
feels so far away...

If only I were a little stronger, would anything have
changed? I feel like it might have, but then again, maybe
not...

But... one thing is for certain... without strength, I can't
do anything.

I can't protect the people important to me... All I can do
is watch as they go far away.
Ha ha... ha ha ha... Really, it's been quite the lesson.
\N<Luda Soldier>What's the matter, we've arrived. Hurry up and go.

\N<Luda Soldier>Hehe... I'm looking forward to it, you know? I heard that
mother and daughter are coming tonight.
\N<Luda Soldier>Yeah, I'm excited about that. It's been a while after all.

\N<Luda Soldier>Which one will you ask for? Or maybe having both is an
option.

\N<Luda Soldier>Hey, wait. You hit me, didn't you? That hurts, apologize,
brat.

\N<Riia>No way. Even if I did hit you, it was just a little, and
it's your fault for not looking where you're going.
\N<Luda Soldier>Huh? What's that, you've got some nerve, don't you?

\N<Luda Soldier>What's with that defiant look? Not enough for you? Want
another punch?

\N<Luda Soldier>Hey, this kid is that one. He's Rozaro's wife's son, no
mistake about it.

\N<Luda Soldier>The captain's wife's son...? What's that supposed to mean,
isn't he the captain's son then?

\N<Luda Soldier>It's all pretty complicated, but hey... heh, I just had a
great idea?
